article.headline: UC Davis 66, Jackson St 58
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. (AP) -- Thomas Juillerat's 20 points, 10 rebounds and four steals helped UC Davis get its first victory of the season, beating Jackson State 66-58 on Saturday night. Ari Warmerdam had 13 points including four key free throws down the stretch for the Aggies (1-6) who played their first six games on the road. The only player in double figures for the Tigers, Trey Johnson had 27 points, five rebounds and three assists to lead Jackson State (4-5). The Aggies hit five 3-pointers and Juillerat had eight points and eight rebounds to lead UC Davis to a 30-23 halftime lead. With seven minutes left in the game, Vince Oliver's 3-point basket gave the Aggies a 55-37 lead until the Tigers went on a 24-6 run to trim the score 61-56 with 44 seconds left. Warmerdam hit four straight free throws with 35 seconds left to seal the victory for the Aggies.
